Elliot would run this to confirm the type of encryption in use.
LUKS analysis on the left; starting the password-cracking attack on the right

The window on the right shows the cracking process. I originally wanted to use Hashcat, one of the most popular password recovery tools, for this scene. Unfortunately, Hashcat didnâ€™t introduce support for LUKS until later in 2016. Elliot ends up running an older tool, bruteforce-luks, that can only guess a few dozen passwords per second.

We close in on the right-hand window as Elliot types:

