This command spins up 8 concurrent threads to guess passwords against the disk image â€œkeyintercept_1.rawâ€, using each line of â€œlyrics.txtâ€ as input.

After the next jump cut, we see that Elliotâ€™s creativity has paid off. Romeroâ€™s password is a line from â€œDonâ€™t Worryâ€ by Curtis Mayfield:

And if thereâ€™s hell below Weâ€™re all gonna go

(Yes, thatâ€™s the same song used in the opening credits for â€œThe Deuceâ€. Complete coincidence!)

Elliot proceeds to mount the encrypted LUKS partition by typing:

